text.tspan: To us, the law isn't blind or neutral.
It's how the wealthy elite perpetuate
existing power structures.
By diversifying the practioners
of law, we offer minorities a
chance to speak truth to power.

text.title: Brown Rabbit
text.tspan: Saying that the status quo is fair and
that it's the minorities who are racist
is simply an act of rhetorical jujitsu ...

text.title: Brown Rabbit
text.tspan: I grew up in a poor minority
inner-city neighborhood
plagued by gun violence.

text.title: Brown Rabbit
text.tspan: My best friend was a transgender
Marxist immigrant denied asylum
after police pulled her over for
driving-while-black and framed
her for distributing crack cocaine.

text.title: Brown Rabbit
text.tspan: .... an attempt by corporate fat-cats to
win support from pig-ignorant Bible-
thumping, gun-toting, cousin-loving...

text.title: Brown Rabbit
text.tspan: ... redneck hicks.

text.title: Brown Rabbit
text.tspan: No no no! Valuing diversity in the
law is not "reverse discrimination"!

text.title: Southern Bunny
text.tspan: Don't make me gut you boy.
